issuesFound.explanation:
`inlineValidator.validate()` marks fields visually but never adds `aria-invalid="true"` (or removes it on success), so screen readers do not receive error state information.  
Fix (inside the validation loop in `validateField`):  
```javascript
if (!result.valid) {
  setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'true');
  // existing error UI …
} else {
  removeAttr(field, 'aria-invalid');
}
```

